<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/739</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-24T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>436. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DAV1">Dye</persName>
                                [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 52. Your undated No. 989, received August 11, <hi rend="italic">re</hi> corkmakers’ agreement.<note n="2" xml:id="d301fn2">Not
                                    printed.</note> We have no record of any cable despatched to you
                                    <pb facs="0364" n="1198" xml:id="pg_1198"/> on July 24, 6 p.m.,
                                and numbered 396. If you refer to our No. 396, July 26, 4 p.m., then
                                you are authorized to sign, provided the final form of the agreement
                                is identical with the draft submitted to the War Trade Board by
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>
                                in his despatch of June 7,<note n="1" xml:id="d301fn1">See footnote
                                    1, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1188">p.
                                        1188</ref>.</note> which he tells us he has sent to you. If
                                there have been any modifications of this draft, cable them to us
                                and do not sign until you are further authorized.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>